OPPOSITION TO the European Central Bank’s plans for quantitative easing has been split along north-south lines in the euro zone. But are these concerns justified? Journalist and author Matthew Syed explains why thinking is more creative in organisations where the staff are diverse. And The Economist’s Wall Street correspondent, Alice Fulwood, plays a round of poker with entrepreneur Bryn Kenney, who tops the world’s All-Time Money List. Simon Long hosts. Runtime: 23min Please subscribe to The Economist for full access to print, digital and audio editions: www.economist.com/radiooffer    Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google | Stitcher | TuneIn